‚úÖ 1. Check Firewall on the Server

On the server (20.20.20.82), allow MySQL port:

sudo firewall-cmd --permanent --add-port=3306/tcp
sudo firewall-cmd --reload

To test quickly (temporarily disable firewall):
sudo systemctl stop firewalld

‚úÖ 2. Ensure Port 3306 Is Reachable
From the client machine (where Workbench is), test with:
telnet 20.20.20.82 3306

or (on Windows PowerShell):
Test-NetConnection -ComputerName 20.20.20.82 -Port 3306


üîê FIREWALL COMMANDS FOR MySQL (PORT 3306)
üîπ Check if firewalld is running
sudo systemctl status firewalld

üîπ Allow MySQL port (3306) permanently
sudo firewall-cmd --permanent --add-port=3306/tcp
sudo firewall-cmd --reload

üîπ Check if port 3306 is open
sudo firewall-cmd --list-ports

You should see:
3306/tcp

üîπ Remove MySQL port rule (if needed)
sudo firewall-cmd --permanent --remove-port=3306/tcp
sudo firewall-cmd --reload


‚úÖ 2. On Linux with iptables (older systems)
üîπ Allow port 3306

sudo iptables -A INPUT -p tcp --dport 3306 -j ACCEPT

üîπ Save iptables rules (persistent after reboot)
On CentOS/RHEL:
sudo service iptables save

üîπ List current iptables rules
sudo iptables -L -n

‚úÖ 3. On Ubuntu/Debian with ufw
üîπ Enable UFW (if not already)
sudo ufw enable

üîπ Allow MySQL port
sudo ufw allow 3306/tcp

üîπ Check firewall status
sudo ufw status

‚úÖ 4. On Windows Firewall
üîπ Open MySQL Port (3306) in Windows

Go to Control Panel > Windows Defender Firewall
Click on Advanced Settings
Select Inbound Rules > New Rule
Choose Port
Select TCP and enter port 3306
Allow the connection
Apply to Domain, Private, Public
Name the rule (e.g., "MySQL 3306")

üîπ Verify the port is open:
Use PowerShell:
Test-NetConnection -ComputerName <server-ip> -Port 3306

‚úÖ BONUS: Disable Firewall Temporarily (For Testing Only)

‚ö†Ô∏è Do this only temporarily to test MySQL connectivity
üîπ CentOS/RHEL:
sudo systemctl stop firewalld

üîπ Ubuntu/Debian:
sudo ufw disable

‚úÖ Quick Summary of Most Common Commands
| OS/Firewall | Allow MySQL Port                                       |
| ----------- | ------------------------------------------------------ |
| Firewalld   | `sudo firewall-cmd --permanent --add-port=3306/tcp`    |
| UFW         | `sudo ufw allow 3306/tcp`                              |
| iptables    | `sudo iptables -A INPUT -p tcp --dport 3306 -j ACCEPT` |
| Windows     | Add inbound rule for TCP port 3306                     |



